               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; name of the scribe; incipits of Text I and its subsections (fols. 20v, 21v, 26v, 27r, 39v, 50v); incipits of Texts II, III; notes in the upper margin of some fols.; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals; numbers of the Miracles.&#xD;
In the incipit page of Texts I and III (fols. 2r, 83r), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita represents the first of the two sub-types of the Däbrä Libanos recension of the Gädlä Täklä Haymanot (close, but not identical to the published text of the Vita, s. E.A.W. BUDGE (ed., tr.), The Life and Miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the Version of Dabra Lîbânôs..., London 1906).</note>
                  </msItem>
